<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.ezboard.com/help/user/customsignature.html">www.ezboard.com/help/user...ature.html</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
A custom signature is one of the many tools used to express your unique identity on the communities you visit. After you create a custom signature, you can display it at the end of each post you make. Make it as simple or as complex as you’d like, from just one line of text to vivid imagery showing off your artistic talents.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:orange;font-size:medium;">Key Information</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
<br>
1. Only ezSupporters can use HTML in their Custom Signature. Both ezSupporters and Free Users are allowed ezcodes. If you would like more than text in your Custom Signature please click the highlighted link for information on how to use HTML or ezCodes.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.ezboard.com/help/user/html_tutorial.html">www.ezboard.com/help/user...orial.html</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.ezboard.com/help/user/ezcodes_tutorial.html">www.ezboard.com/help/user...orial.html</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
 <br>
2. All users have the convenience of a Formatting Tool available when they create their ezcode custom signature. You do not need to know ezcodes to create an original Custom Signature with this tool. ezSupporters have the added benefit of an HTML formatting tool. <br>
<br>
3. Unclosed tables or other HTML or ezCode tags in a Custom Signature can ruin an entire page of posts. Make sure to close all tags and try to avoid using tables in your signature to prevent disrupting a community. <br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:orange;font-size:medium;">User: How to create your Custom Signature</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
<br>
Your custom signature may be displayed at the end of every post. You can use HTML (ezSupporter) or ezcodes (ezSupporter and Free Users) to include an image, bold text, colors, etc. (up to 2000 characters). The examples below are in ezcodes.<br>
<br>
Note: If you wish to make a carriage return, use the ezcode tag [*br] (without the *). If including an image, please make sure they are small in size.<br>
<br>
1. Log in to your Control Center and click on the Account Preferences link. <br>
<br>
2. You are now in a new screen. Scroll down to the area that says Custom Signature. You can now begin adding your Custom Signature code. If you want to use an image, you can type the exact URL to your image in the field. If you prefer to display your name, a quote or some text as your signature, type it in the given field. <br>
<br>
3. For help creating an ezcode signature click on the Launch Tool link next to the ezcode radio button.With the Formatting Tool you can create a flawless custom signature with ease. ezSupporters have the option to launch the HTML formatting tool when creating HTML signatures. <br>
